Description: each process initially assume it is the leader. The process then sends a message to all its neighbors, informing them of its ID and the fact that it believes it is the leader. Upon receiving this message, each process compares its own ID with the received ID. If the received ID is greater, the process updates its own ID with the received ID and continues the flooding process. This continues until the flood reaches a stable state where no further updates occur.
